  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "I'd like to be able to override a non-lifecycle component method without React throwing. Something like:\n\n``` js\nvar MyMixin = {\n  someMethod: function () {\n    // the default behavior\n  }\n};\n\nvar MyComponent = {\n  mixins: [ MyMixin ],\n  someMethod: function () {\n    if (needsToOverrideMixinBehavior) {\n      // override the mixin's behavior\n    } else {\n      MyMixin.someMethod.apply(this, arguments);\n    }\n  }\n};\n```\n\nIdeally, this would eventually be doable using [some sort of hierarchy system](https://github.com/reactjs/react-future/blob/master/01%20-%20Core/02%20-%20Mixins.js) (and possibly `super`), but for now I just want the ability to override a mixin method.\n",
